The paper focuses on a dataset for training and evaluating robotic visual grasp detection algorithms, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The dataset is composed of diverse objects, which requires computer vision techniques for object recognition (cs.CV) and machine learning algorithms for grasp detection (cs.AI, cs.LG). Additionally, the dataset can be used for testing robotic manipulation systems, which falls under the field of control systems (cs.SY).
